column7: "The powder data were collected at 60 °C"…"The ISD triblock copolymer studied in this report has volumefractions of 0.40/0.41/0.19, respectively and a molecular weight of 41 000 g/mol. We show that the morphology of this triblock is a core-shell gyroid structure with an Ia3hd space-group symmetry"

"Figure 3 SAXS data from the parent PI−PS diblock copolymer (90 °C, top), and SAXS (155 °C, middle) and TEM (OsO4 stained, bottom) results from a PI−PS−PEO triblock copolymer containing 9.8 vol % PEO. These results are consistent with two-domain (PI and mixed PS/PEO) lamellae (LAM2) morphologies."

"Figure 4 SAXS (180 °C, top) and TEM (OsO4 stained, bottom) data from the PI−PS−PEO triblock copolymer containing 30% PEO. These results are consistent with a three-domain lamellae (LAM3) morphology."
